      "content": "thanks. i just ran that through the audit tool and it gave it a score of 4. it's actually failing—the minimum threshold to pass the cloudscale audit is 15. \n\ncan you expand on this? i really don't want you to just add junk headers like \"Section 1\", \"Section 2\" etc. that's obviously bad. try to break the documentation down into more granular, professional sub-topics so the header count hits at least 15. keep it technically sound so devs actually find it helpful.",
