      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "# User Profile Retrieval Endpoint: GET /user\n\n## 1. Endpoint Summary and Purpose\nThis section details the primary function of the `/user` endpoint, which is to fetch the authenticated user's profile data.\n\n## 2. Authentication Requirements\n### 2.1 Token Validation\nDetails on the required authorization header format and token validity checks.\n\n### 2.2 Scope and Permissions\nDefining which scopes are necessary for successful invocation of this endpoint.\n\n## 3. Request Specification\n### 3.1 HTTP Method and Path\nSpecifying the exact `GET /user` structure.\n\n### 3.2 Request Parameters\nListing any optional query parameters, even if none are currently used.\n\n## 4. Response Structure and Data Model\n### 4.1 Success Response (200 OK)\nA detailed breakdown of the expected JSON payload structure.\n\n### 4.2 Field Definitions\nIn-depth descriptions for `id`, `email`, and `name` fields.\n\n## 5. Error Handling Protocols\n### 5.1 Client Errors (4xx)\nCovering scenarios like invalid tokens or missing credentials.\n\n### 5.2 Server Errors (5xx)",
